title: Mayor Walsh catches fish ‘like Malcolm Butler’ in visit to Seattle - Politics
text:
Like many visitors to the famed Pike Place Fish Market in Seattle, Boston Mayor Marty Walsh was challenged to catch a slippery fish thrown in his direction.
The mayor decided to channel a hometown hero known for his own interception of a Seattle throw.
“Caught it like Malcolm Butler,” Walsh said in a tweet .
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Yes, Walsh rubbed some salt in the wound that was the Seahawks last-second Super Bowl loss to the Patriots during a visit to Seattle on Monday. Walsh’s visit to the northwest was part of a summit with Seattle Mayor Ed Murray and tech executives that focused on how growing cities can maintain a high quality of life.
#Seattle pike place fish @marty_walsh catching the pass! #mapoli #bospoli #city2city @collegebounddot
A photo posted by Mark Culliton (@markly64) on Oct 18, 2015 at 4:33pm PDT
It wasn’t all snarky teasing for the mayor. Walsh also said that Seahawks fans were being “very classy” during his visit.
